(49, 'A look at Swara Bhasker’s wedding wardrobe. In pics', 'Swara Bhasker', '60,61,62,63', 'Delhi', 'img_641ead952ec02.jpg', '<h2 class=\"Photo_kicker__pnqUP\" style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; font-family: Rubik, helvatica, Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: normal;\">After celebrating her union with Fahad Ahmad in a grand multi-day soiree, Swara Bhasker has been sharing stunning photos from her wedding celebrations on Instagram. Here\'s a look at her wedding wardrobe.</h2><div class=\"Photo_photoCard__list__F08Fh\" style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(226, 226, 226); margin-bottom: var(--widgetgap); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Rubik, helvatica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><div id=\"photo_1\" class=\"PhotoCard_photoCard__uE7hP phototype PhotoCard_phototype__zvqG7\"><div class=\"PhotoCard_card__pic__axT6x\" style=\"margin-bottom: var(--magrin15); position: relative;\"><img src=\"https://akm-img-a-in.tosshub.com/indiatoday/images/photo_gallery/202303/335641284_5994720323916653_2690660976002337997_n_0.jpg?VersionId=UwWWAYos1cI67IHtcKtNjUYWt9OSf0WL&amp;size=686:*\" title=\"335641284_5994720323916653_2690660976002337997_n.jpg\" alt=\"335641284_5994720323916653_2690660976002337997_n.jpg\" width=\"1440\" height=\"1800\" class=\"img_container\" data-imgnum=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width: 100%; display: block; border-radius: 5px; border: 1px solid var(--widgetbordercolor); width: 688.4px; height: auto;\"><div class=\"article__type PhotoCard_article__type__dNLO0\" style=\"position: absolute; bottom: 10px; left: 10px; width: 70px; height: 36px; background-color: var(--brandtextcolor); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 20px; display: flex; -webkit-box-align: center; align-items: center; justify-content: space-evenly; border-radius: 3px;\"><span class=\"typedata\">1/8</span></div></div><div class=\"PhotoCard_card__details__3Le4m\" style=\"padding-bottom: 20px;\"><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; color: var(--primarytextcolor);\"></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; color: var(--primarytextcolor);\">Swara Bhasker, who recently got married to political activist Fahad Ahmad, has been sharing stunning photos from their wedding celebrations.&nbsp;</p><p></p></div></div></div>', '81', '19', '25-03-23 09:15:17', '25-03-23 09:15:17'),
(52, 'Jimin of BTS is captivating and dreamy in the new music video, Like Crazy. Video Out', 'BTS', '62,63,64,65,66', 'Korea', 'img_641eae1d9b3a8.jpg', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--storyparagap); font-size: 18px; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Rubik, helvatica, Arial, sans-serif;\"><a title=\"Bhavna Agarwal\" href=\"https://www.indiatoday.in/author/bhavna-agarwal\" style=\"color: var(--linkcolor); text-decoration-line: none;\">By Bhavna Agarwal</a>: BTS member Jimin finally makes his solo album debut with Face.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.indiatoday.in/lifestyle/what-s-hot/story/jimin-of-bts-shares-the-first-poster-of-title-track-like-crazy-details-inside-2349064-2023-03-20\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: var(--linkcolor); text-decoration-line: none;\">The album consisting of six songs is now available on all streaming platforms.</a>&nbsp;Apart from the audio, the vocalist of BTS has also dropped the music video for Like Crazy, which is the main track for the album. The song has been written in collaboration with many artists, including Jimin and RM as well.</p><h3 style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 20px; line-height: 26px; font-weight: 600; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Rubik, helvatica, Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: normal; text-transform: none;\"><strong>LIKE CRAZY MV OUT</strong></h3><p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--storyparagap); font-size: 18px; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Rubik, helvatica, Arial, sans-serif;\">Jimin had earlier specified that Like Crazy was inspired by one of his favourite movies. The music video concentrates on the alluring charm of the BTS member as he feels trapped in the past. Through the music video, Jimin uses crowded space to show the loneliness he embraces as a trapped soul. “I’d rather be/Lost in the lights/I’m outta my mind,” Jimin ad libs in the chorus.</p>', '81', '17', '25-03-23 09:17:33', '25-03-23 09:17:33'),
(53, 'Have lingering sore throat? These home remedies could help you recover faster', ' Anees Hussain', '66,67', 'Mumbai', 'img_641eafadc413d.jpg', '<p><div class=\"jsx-99cc083358cc2e2d  Story_w__100__e1YfC\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; grid-template-columns: 1fr; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Rubik, helvatica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><div class=\"jsx-99cc083358cc2e2d Story_strykicker__S0QMt story-kicker\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></div></div></p><h1 class=\"jsx-99cc083358cc2e2d Story_strytitle__MYXmR\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; font-size: 30px; line-height: 38px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-weight: 600; font-family: Rubik, helvatica, Arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--storyparagap); font-size: 18px; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-weight: 400;\"><a title=\"Daphne Clarance\" href=\"https://www.indiatoday.in/author/daphne-clarance\" style=\"color: var(--linkcolor);\">By Daphne Clarance</a>: Almost every second person this season has been suffering from an itchy feeling in their throats.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--storyparagap); font-size: 18px; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-weight: 400;\">With seasonal flu like the H3N2 influenza virus being reported, cases of Covid-19 and Adenovirus are also on the rise, people are experiencing sore throat,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.indiatoday.in/health/story/spring-influenza-cases-rise-with-prolonged-cough-and-breathlessness-symptoms-precautions-treatment-2341128-2023-03-01\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: var(--linkcolor); text-decoration-line: underline;\">lingering cough and fever</a>&nbsp;after getting infected.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--storyparagap); font-size: 18px; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-weight: 400;\">To recover from a sore throat or cough faster, experts suggest letting it rest and adding foods that will give your throat moisture.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--storyparagap); font-size: 18px; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-weight: 400;\">According to Dr Savyasachi Saxena, Senior Consultant &amp; HOD, ENT, Fortis Hospital, Noida, the treatment is avoiding any kind if irritants getting into your throat.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--storyparagap); font-size: 18px; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-weight: 400;\">\"If there is any coughing or some other symptoms&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.indiatoday.in/health/story/h3n2-virus-outbreak-india-symptoms-treatment-precautions-vaccine-flu-2343578-2023-03-07\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: var(--linkcolor); text-decoration-line: underline;\">persisting with a sore throat</a>, then that has to be treated with medication. However, with just a sore throat that feels itchy, you can do certain things at home to relieve the pain,\" Dr Saxena told indiatoday.in.</p></h1>', '82', '23', '25-03-23 09:24:13', '25-03-23 09:24:13'),
(54, 'Wheelchair-bound kids with fatal genetic disorder protest seeking faster treatment', 'Poulomi Ghosh', '58,59,60,61', 'New Delhi', 'img_641eb006b9567.jpg', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--storyparagap); font-size: 18px; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Rubik, helvatica, Arial, sans-serif;\"><a title=\"India Today Bureau\" href=\"https://www.indiatoday.in/author/india-today-bureau\" style=\"color: var(--linkcolor); text-decoration-line: none;\">By India Today Bureau</a>: Parents of children suffering from Duchenne Muscular Dystrophy (DMD), a fatal genetic disease, gathered at Jantar Mantar, Delhi, on March 24, 2023, to raise awareness about the disease and register their anguish against the government’s apathy. The parents and others who joined wore white t-shirts and badges with “Save Our Sons” written on them, as the disease mostly affects boys.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--storyparagap); font-size: 18px; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Rubik, helvatica, Arial, sans-serif;\">Addressing the devastating effects of the fatal disease and the urgent need for action, the event saw hundreds of wheelchair-bound children diagnosed with the disease and their parents gathered from all over the country.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--storyparagap); font-size: 18px; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Rubik, helvatica, Arial, sans-serif;\">Parents demanded in unison to expedite the process of bringing in experimental treatments like gene therapy and exon skipping to India. Their demands included the creation of an empowered panel of health ministry officials, representatives from the DMD parents, and the provision of free medications and physiotherapy facilities to all DMD children.</p>', '82', '23', '25-03-23 09:25:42', '25-03-23 09:25:42'),
(55, '\'Vampiric overconsumption\': India likely to be severely affected by water scarcity, says UN report', 'Poulomi Ghosh', '59,60,61', 'USA', 'img_641eb068ec5c2.jpg', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--storyparagap); font-size: 18px; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Rubik, helvatica, Arial, sans-serif;\"><a title=\"India Today Environment Desk\" href=\"https://www.indiatoday.in/author/india-today-environment-desk\" style=\"color: var(--linkcolor); text-decoration-line: none;\">By India Today Environment Desk</a>: India is expected to be the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.indiatoday.in/magazine/cover-story/story/20210329-the-great-indian-thirst-1781280-2021-03-20\" target=\"_self\" style=\"color: var(--linkcolor); text-decoration-line: none;\">most severely affected nation by water scarcity</a>&nbsp;by 2050, a UN report said. The United Nations World Water Development Report 2023 issued on Tuesday ahead of the UN 2023 Water Conference, said that around 80% of people living under water stress lived in Asia, in particular, northeast China, as well as India and Pakistan.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--storyparagap); font-size: 18px; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Rubik, helvatica, Arial, sans-serif;\">The global urban population facing water scarcity is projected to increase from 933 million in 2016 to 1.7-2.4 billion people in 2050 with India projected to be the most severely affected, the report said.</p>', '84', '29', '25-03-23 09:27:20', '25-03-23 09:27:20'),
(56, 'UN chief’s call for ambition on climate gets muted response', 'Ritu Maria Johny', '59,60,61,62,63', 'USA', 'img_641eb08e24e2d.jpg', '<div class=\"jsx-99cc083358cc2e2d Story_stry__highlights__9IosL\" style=\"margin-bottom: var(--storyparagap); padding: var(--widgetgap); background-color: var(--bodybg); border-radius: 5px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Rubik, helvatica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><h3 class=\"jsx-99cc083358cc2e2d Story_title__dp5qB\" style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1;\">In Short</h3><ul class=\"jsx-99cc083358cc2e2d Story_highlights__list__FRRjs\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 1.5em; list-style-position: inside; text-indent: -1.5em;\"><li class=\"jsx-99cc083358cc2e2d\" style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; line-height: 22px;\">Guterres’ call came in a video message responding to a new UN report</li><li class=\"jsx-99cc083358cc2e2d\" style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; line-height: 22px;\">China is targeting 2060 and India has set a deadline of 2070 for Net-Zero</li><li class=\"jsx-99cc083358cc2e2d\" style=\"line-height: 22px;\">US and the European Union are currently aiming for net zero by 2050</li></ul></div><div class=\"jsx-99cc083358cc2e2d Story_description__fq_4S description\" style=\"margin-bottom: var(--widgetgap); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Rubik, helvatica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--storyparagap); font-size: 18px; line-height: 28px; color: var(--primarytextcolor);\"><a title=\"Associated Press\" href=\"https://www.indiatoday.in/author/associated-press-0\" style=\"color: var(--linkcolor); text-decoration-line: none;\">By Associated Press</a>: Senior government officials at a climate meeting in Copenhagen gave a muted response Tuesday to calls from the head of the United Nations for countries to show greater ambition when it comes to reducing greenhouse gas emissions.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--storyparagap); font-size: 18px; line-height: 28px; color: var(--primarytextcolor);\">U.N. Secretary-General AntÃ³nio Guterres urged rich countries Monday to bring forward their target for achieving net zero emissions as close as possible to 2040, and for emerging economies to aim for a date as close as possible to 2050. This would be a significant shifting of the goal posts: the United States and the European Union are currently aiming for net zero by 2050, while China is targeting 2060 and India has set a deadline of 2070.</p></div>', '84', '30', '25-03-23 09:27:58', '25-03-23 09:27:58'),
(57, 'Dummy title', ' Anees Hussain', '58,59,60,61,62', 'New Delhi', 'img_641eb0b31dbc1.jpg', '<div class=\"jsx-99cc083358cc2e2d Story_stry__highlights__9IosL\" style=\"margin-bottom: var(--storyparagap); padding: var(--widgetgap); background-color: var(--bodybg); border-radius: 5px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Rubik, helvatica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><h3 class=\"jsx-99cc083358cc2e2d Story_title__dp5qB\" style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1;\">In Short</h3><ul class=\"jsx-99cc083358cc2e2d Story_highlights__list__FRRjs\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 1.5em; list-style-position: inside; text-indent: -1.5em;\"><li class=\"jsx-99cc083358cc2e2d\" style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; line-height: 22px;\">Climate change is exacerbating the problems</li><li class=\"jsx-99cc083358cc2e2d\" style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; line-height: 22px;\">More than 381 forest fires were reported in March in India</li><li class=\"jsx-99cc083358cc2e2d\" style=\"line-height: 22px;\">Traditionally, forest fires have been used to manage forests</li></ul></div><div class=\"jsx-99cc083358cc2e2d Story_description__fq_4S description\" style=\"margin-bottom: var(--widgetgap); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Rubik, helvatica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--storyparagap); font-size: 18px; line-height: 28px; color: var(--primarytextcolor);\"><a title=\"Abinash Mohanty\" href=\"https://www.indiatoday.in/author/abinash-mohanty\" style=\"color: var(--linkcolor); text-decoration-line: none;\">By Abinash Mohanty</a>: The 2023 International Forests Day theme is forests and health. While it emphasizes forest-led services for health and well-being, it re-emphasizes the role of forests in mitigating climate risks, purifying our air, and sequestering carbon, among others.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--storyparagap); font-size: 18px; line-height: 28px; color: var(--primarytextcolor);\">Our forests define India’s way of living, but unfortunately- the loss of forests in recent years has ravaged lives, livelihoods, and economies. Climate change, coupled with anthropocentric landscape planning, has exacerbated the impacts. 2023 has already been a testament to the fact that a climate crisis is upon us with the scorching irregular February and March heat waves, incessant rainfall, and hailstorms that have disrupted agricultural productivity by co-opting central and northern parts of India.</p></div>', '84', '28', '25-03-23 09:28:35', '25-03-23 09:30:25'),
(58, 'new title', 'Poulomi Ghosh', '59,60,61,62,63,64,65', 'Delhi', 'img_641eb15669d83.jpg', '<div class=\"jsx-99cc083358cc2e2d Story_stry__highlights__9IosL\" style=\"margin-bottom: var(--storyparagap); padding: var(--widgetgap); background-color: var(--bodybg); border-radius: 5px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Rubik, helvatica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><h3 class=\"jsx-99cc083358cc2e2d Story_title__dp5qB\" style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1;\">In Short</h3><ul class=\"jsx-99cc083358cc2e2d Story_highlights__list__FRRjs\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 1.5em; list-style-position: inside; text-indent: -1.5em;\"><li class=\"jsx-99cc083358cc2e2d\" style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; line-height: 22px;\">Climate change is exacerbating the problems</li><li class=\"jsx-99cc083358cc2e2d\" style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; line-height: 22px;\">More than 381 forest fires were reported in March in India</li><li class=\"jsx-99cc083358cc2e2d\" style=\"line-height: 22px;\">Traditionally, forest fires have been used to manage forests</li></ul></div><div class=\"jsx-99cc083358cc2e2d Story_description__fq_4S description\" style=\"margin-bottom: var(--widgetgap); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Rubik, helvatica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--storyparagap); font-size: 18px; line-height: 28px; color: var(--primarytextcolor);\"><a title=\"Abinash Mohanty\" href=\"https://www.indiatoday.in/author/abinash-mohanty\" style=\"color: var(--linkcolor); text-decoration-line: none;\">By Abinash Mohanty</a>: The 2023 International Forests Day theme is forests and health. While it emphasizes forest-led services for health and well-being, it re-emphasizes the role of forests in mitigating climate risks, purifying our air, and sequestering carbon, among others.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--storyparagap); font-size: 18px; line-height: 28px; color: var(--primarytextcolor);\">Our forests define India’s way of living, but unfortunately- the loss of forests in recent years has ravaged lives, livelihoods, and economies. Climate change, coupled with anthropocentric landscape planning, has exacerbated the impacts. 2023 has already been a testament to the fact that a climate crisis is upon us with the scorching irregular February and March heat waves, incessant rainfall, and hailstorms that have disrupted agricultural productivity by co-opting central and northern parts of India.</p></div>', '84', '29', '25-03-23 09:31:18', '25-03-23 09:33:42'),
(59, '\'Humanity on thin ice\': What did the UN IPCC report warn?', 'Ritu Maria Johny', '59,60,61,62', 'Delhi', 'img_641eb19a9e2fe.jpg', '<div class=\"jsx-99cc083358cc2e2d Story_stry__highlights__9IosL\" style=\"margin-bottom: var(--storyparagap); padding: var(--widgetgap); background-color: var(--bodybg); border-radius: 5px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Rubik, helvatica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><h3 class=\"jsx-99cc083358cc2e2d Story_title__dp5qB\" style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1;\">In Short</h3><ul class=\"jsx-99cc083358cc2e2d Story_highlights__list__FRRjs\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 1.5em; list-style-position: inside; text-indent: -1.5em;\"><li class=\"jsx-99cc083358cc2e2d\" style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; line-height: 22px;\">UN chief called for an end to new fossil fuel exploration</li><li class=\"jsx-99cc083358cc2e2d\" style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; line-height: 22px;\">Guterres called for rich countries to accelerate their target for achieving net zero emissions</li><li class=\"jsx-99cc083358cc2e2d\" style=\"line-height: 22px;\">After 1.5 degrees “the risks are starting to pile on,” said report co-author</li></ul></div><div class=\"jsx-99cc083358cc2e2d Story_description__fq_4S description\" style=\"margin-bottom: var(--widgetgap); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Rubik, helvatica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--storyparagap); font-size: 18px; line-height: 28px; color: var(--primarytextcolor);\"><a title=\"India Today Environment Desk\" href=\"https://www.indiatoday.in/author/india-today-environment-desk\" style=\"color: var(--linkcolor); text-decoration-line: none;\">By India Today Environment Desk</a>: The Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (IPCC) in its latest assessment has warned that the planet is on the brink of irreversible damage to the climate.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--storyparagap); font-size: 18px; line-height: 28px; color: var(--primarytextcolor);\">The report concluded that to stay under the warming limit set in Paris, the world needs to cut 60 per cent of its greenhouse gas emissions by 2035, compared with 2019, adding a new target not previously mentioned in six previous reports issued since 2018.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--storyparagap); font-size: 18px; line-height: 28px; color: var(--primarytextcolor);\">The sixth assessment report summarises the state of knowledge of climate</p></div>', '84', '28', '25-03-23 09:32:26', '25-03-23 09:32:26'),
(60, 'PM Modi to inaugurate 13.71-km Metro line in Bengaluru today', ' Anees Hussain', '61,62,63,64', 'Mumbai', 'img_641eb29440a15.jpg', '<div class=\"editor-share\" style=\"border: 0px; outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: &quot;Droid Serif&quot;, serif;\"><div class=\"editor editor-date-logo  editor-details-new-change\" id=\"storycenterbyline\" style=\"padding-bottom: 15px; border: none; outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; font-size: 13px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 20px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; min-height: auto; border-radius: 5px; position: static; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center;\"><div style=\"border: 0px; outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline;\">By:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://indianexpress.com/agency/express-web-desk/\" style=\"font-size: 12px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: 0px 0px; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; line-height: 20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-weight: 700;\">Express Web Desk</a><br>Bengaluru |&nbsp;<span itemprop=\"dateModified\" content=\"2023-03-25T07:55:32+05:30\" style=\"border: 0px; outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; font-size: 12px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(72, 72, 72); line-height: 16px;\">Updated: March 25, 2023 07:55 IST</span></div><div class=\"brand-logo\" style=\"margin-top: 5px; border: 0px; outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; float: right;\"><img src=\"https://indianexpress.com/wp-content/themes/indianexpress/images/icon-newsguard.svg\" width=\"120px\" height=\"18px\" alt=\"Newsguard\" style=\"border-style: initial; outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; max-width: 100%;\"></div></d